oai_dc:dc.dc:title: The Overdue Calf Delivery
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Andrews, Arch
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: overdue calf delivery
dead calf
salvage
heifer
cost
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: In the typical bovine practice, the overdue calf delivery occurs all too often, with the calf having been dead from a few minutes to a few weeks when presented for delivery. Since we are dealing with a salvage situation, the welfare of the heifer or cow and cost to the owner are of primary consideration.
